<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-453-004  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 453 004.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  March 1990 v7 n3 p207(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Preditor 1.0. (Software Review) (Evatec Software) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wayner, Peter.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Evatec Software's $90 text editor for programmers, Preditor 1.0,is a comprehensive editor for the capable programmer.andP;  Preditorincludes a macro language for defining functions and controlswhich is also a complete programming language.andP;  The macro languagealso supports the constructs of simple programming languages suchas C. However, Preditor's macro language is slow and the syntaxuses cryptic characters.andP;  The text editor is loaded with extrafeatures and the editor's main window offers numerous options formoving around a file easily.andP;  An extensively cross-referenced,75-page manual comes with Preditor and is additionally availableon-line.andP;  The manual would do well to include more examples in themacro section, but is well-documented in general.andP;  Anidentification feature that automatically formats code is absentfrom Preditor, but one can be created in the macro language.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Evatec Software (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)Preditor (Text editor).andO;Topic:     EvaluationText Editors.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>